data.title: Defined: Boop
data.description: In this episode of Defined, learn what it means to "boop" an opponent from San Francisco Shock's Super, Houston Outlaws' Rawkus, and Los Angeles Gladiators' BigGoose. It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel.Learn more at http://www.Intel.com/OWL

data.title: Overwatch League All-Stars 2019 New Skins Reveal
data.description: See the new skins for Atlantic Mercy and Pacific Lúcio.

data.title: Chillin’ with Geguri and Danny Lim
data.description: Lover of ice cream, Twitter, frogs, and dogs, there are many unique qualities to Kim “Geguri” Se-Yeon. Danny Lim gets the scoop on what’s next for the Shanghai Dragons tank player.

data.title: BigGoose Learns Korean
data.description: Language barriers are one of many obstacles to overcome as a professional Overwatch player. Benjamin “BigGoose” Isohanni is doing his best to bridge that gap between himself and his Korean-speaking teammates on the Los Angeles Gladiators.

data.title: Over The Top Moments | Stage 2 | Week 3 | Day 2 | Overwatch League
The Battle of LA
data.description: Shields Up or Wings Out? The Los Angeles Gladiators and the Los Angeles Valiant have historically duked it out at the Blizzard Arena to see who owns the City of Angels. Who will win this time around?

data.title: My Hero: Tracer
data.description: In this episode of My Hero, learn about Tracer's high-mobility kit from New York Excelsior's Saebyeolbe, San Francisco Shock's Striker, and London Spitfire's Profit. It’s all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Learn more at http://www.Intel.com/OWL

data.title: Meta Report: Stage 1
data.description: Stage 1 of the 2019 Overwatch League was dominated by triple-tank, triple-support team comps. In this episode of the Intel Meta Report, learn the most important facts about the "3-3 meta" that you need to follow the action! It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Learn more at http://www.Intel.

data.title: On Point with Fusions
data.description: Grinding his way through the Path to Pro scene, Cameron “Fusions” Bosworth has made it to the Overwatch League with a commanding presence. Malik sits down with the Boston Uprising main tank to discuss his journey to the League and his expectations for the Uprising this season.

data.title: Ameng – Wrecking Ball Beast
data.description: Ameng of the Chengdu Hunters got the ball rolling on Wrecking Ball in the 2019 Season and won’t stop rolling through his rivals!

data.title: The Think Tank with Fissure, Mano, and Ria
data.description: Fissure of the Seoul Dynasty, Mano of the New York Excelsior, and Ria of the Hangzhou Spark sit down in the Think Tank to discuss the skills required of tank players, favorite tank plays, and advice for all tank players.

data.title: Game/Set with Philadelphia Fusion’s Eqo
data.description: The Philadelphia Fusion’s Eqo explains his optimized settings so you can maximize your damage when jumping into the fray as Genji. This is Game Set brought to you by OMEN by HP.
